<br>
However, it is negligence.  If I'm speeding along the freeway at 75mph in a 55mph zone and not paying attention to how fast I'm going, the highway patrol will still ticket me and penalize me.  I think that this is what's being offered.<br>
<br>
It was a boneheaded thing to do, and I think that if Frayed Knot looked at themselves a bit and were willing to swallow a bit of pride, they'd realize that they're acting in adversity to the community instead of acting to support the community.  Ask.  Communicate.  Take responsibility.  Don't assume everyone is out to get you.  Assume that you are a member of the community and that you have the responsibility to maintain the community.<br>
<br>
Shit happens.  I've seen Noble Blade do things that made me cringe (And gotten some of my own guildies pissed for calling them on it).  I'm just upset that FK didn't go into full 'Yeah, we did it!  Fuck you and your horse!' so that we could spread some hate.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#222222><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/btherathetravelagency.showUserPublicProfile?gid=trivilusnightbladebots>Trivilus Nightblade BotS</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>BotS - Guild Rep</span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#00FFFF>(12/30/02 8:02:16 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=238.topic&index=22>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Blatant?</span><hr size=1> well i had mentioned that BotS would support the fact that FK miss one rotation as punishment since they killed out of order. But i heard tonight that another guild killed Trak out of rotation and was told they would just miss their next spawn and nothing further.<br>
